Some stuff I looked at used a line of champs, the newest entry being the 
pareto front. A while ago I suggested an extension to the idea by 
maintainign a tree of champs in different categories, each leaf node of 
which represents a pareto front, which is maybe were you&#39;re going with 
this. Umm, I think the tree gets a bit unwieldy though since any genome 
that doesn&#39;t have any positive attributes would get assigned as a new 
pareto front coming off of the root node. Maybe you just limit it to 
being a binary (or some arbitrary degree) tree.

